CHAPTER 2: LITERATURE SURVEY 
2.1 EXISTING SYSTEM 
In many educational institutions, alumni management is handled through traditional and 
unstructured methods such as spreadsheets, social media groups, and manual record keeping. 
These systems lack integration and do not provide a centralized platform for maintaining 
alumni data. 
Most existing systems do not offer proper communication channels between alumni and the 
institution. Networking opportunities are limited, and there is no efficient way to track alumni 
achievements or organize events systematically. Job-related information is often shared 
informally, making it difficult for alumni to access relevant opportunities. 
Additionally, donation processes are not streamlined, and there is a lack of transparency and 
ease in contributing to institutional development. These limitations result in weak alumni 
engagement and underutilization of alumni potential. 
2.2 PROPOSED SYSTEM 
The proposed system is a centralized Alumni Association Platform that integrates various 
functionalities into a single web and mobile-based application. The system is designed to 
overcome the limitations of the existing system by providing a structured and user-friendly 
environment for alumni interaction. 
The platform enables alumni to register, update their profiles, and connect with other alumni. 
It includes features such as an alumni directory, job portal, networking hub, donation system, 
and event management module. The system also allows institutions to track alumni 
achievements and success stories. 
By providing secure access, real-time updates, and easy navigation, the proposed system 
enhances communication and collaboration among alumni. It ensures efficient data 
management and creates opportunities for professional growth and institutional development. 
