CHAPTER 3: REQUIREMENTS ANALYSIS 
3.1 METHOD USED FOR REQUIREMENTS ANALYSIS 
Requirement analysis is the process of identifying and understanding the needs of users and 
the system. In the proposed Alumni Association Platform, multiple methods are used to gather 
and analyse requirements effectively. 
Firstly, requirement gathering through observation and analysis of existing systems is 
performed to understand the limitations of current alumni management methods and identify 
user needs. 
Secondly, the Use Case approach is used as the primary method to define interactions between 
users (actors) and the system. This helps in clearly identifying functional requirements such as 
login, job posting, event management, and networking. 
Additionally, functional decomposition is applied to divide the system into smaller modules 
such as registration, job portal, donation system, and event management, making the system 
easier to design and implement. 
These methods together ensure that the system requirements are clear, structured, and aligned 
with user expectations. 
3.2 DATA REQUIREMENTS 
Data requirements specify the type of data that must be stored, processed, and managed by the 
system. The Alumni Association Platform requires the following data: 
• Alumni Information: Name, email, contact number, graduation year, department, job 
profile, and location 
• Authentication Data: Username and password for login purposes 
• Job Details: Job title, company name, job description, and eligibility criteria 
• Event Information: Event name, date, time, location, and description 
• Donation Records: Donor name, amount, transaction details 
• Feedback and Survey Data: User feedback, suggestions, and responses 
7 
The system must ensure secure storage, easy retrieval, and proper management of all data. 
3.3 FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS 
Functional requirements define the specific operations and functionalities that the system must 
perform. The key functional requirements are: 
• The system shall allow alumni to register and login securely 
• The system shall allow users to update and manage their profiles 
• The system shall provide an alumni directory for searching users based on various criteria 
• The system shall allow alumni to post job opportunities and apply for jobs 
• The system shall enable networking and communication among alumni 
• The system shall allow users to view and register for events and reunions 
• The system shall provide a secure donation portal for financial contributions 
• The system shall display alumni achievements and success stories 
• The system shall allow users to submit feedback and participate in surveys 
3.4 NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS 
Non-functional requirements define the quality attributes and performance of the system. These 
include: 
• Performance: The system should handle multiple users efficiently and provide fast response 
time 
• Security: User data should be protected using authentication and secure protocols 
• Usability: The system should have a simple and user-friendly interface 
• Scalability: The system should be able to support an increasing number of users in the 
future 
• Reliability: The system should function consistently without errors or failures 
• Availability: The system should be accessible anytime through web and mobile platforms 
