Introduction 
A sequence diagram represents the interaction between objects in a sequential order. It shows 
how messages are exchanged among system components during a process. In this project, the 
sequence diagram represents the job application process. 
Description 
The process starts when the alumni logs into the system. The system validates user credentials 
through the Job Module. After successful authentication, the alumni views available jobs. The 
Job Module retrieves job data from the database and displays job details to the user. The alumni 
then applies for a selected job, and the system stores the application in the database. Finally, a 
confirmation message is sent to the alumni. 
