CHAPTER 6 – CONCLUSION & FUTURE WORK 
6.1 LIMITATION OF PROJECT 
Introduction 
Every software system has certain limitations based on available resources, development time, 
technology, and project scope. The current version of the Alumni Association Platform is 
designed to provide essential functionalities for alumni interaction, job management, event 
participation, donations, and feedback handling. 
Although the system performs efficiently, some limitations still exist. 
Limitations of the Project 
Limited Security Features 
The current system provides basic authentication and validation features. Advanced security 
mechanisms such as two-factor authentication and encryption are not implemented. 
Limited Payment Gateway Integration 
The donation module currently supports basic payment handling and does not include advanced 
payment gateway integration. 
Internet Dependency 
The platform requires an active internet connection for accessing web and mobile 
functionalities. 
Limited Real-Time Communication 
The current system does not support real-time chat or instant messaging between alumni users. 
Scalability Constraints 
The project is designed for academic purposes and may require optimization for handling a 
very large number of users in real-world deployment. 
